          <p>Since Airbnb use many of the features a web developer should know, i.e. search by dates, maps, payment, users of different specifications, sign up and log in/log out, grids, comments and ratings, we spent some time at Le Wagon building a copycat. My team and I built <%= link_to "Limelite", "https://cinema-airbnb-clone.herokuapp.com/", class: "project-link" %>, an MVC app that allows users to search for film events using location, buy tickets for the ones they like the look of, as well as host events themselves. We were working on tight timings with this app, having only four full days for production. The app is hosted by Heroku.</p>
          <p>Although the business standard is mobile first, we knew we would present this app on desktop only, and due to time constraints, we did not make this site responsive. Note that since this isnâ€™t a live site it contains limited seeds, added only for our team to be able to present. To ensure you get search results, enter Manchester on Halloween 2019.</p>
